values:
Hmmm, I don't know how I&nbsp;feel about that in a bigger sense, but I&nbsp;know it is true in my household that I&nbsp;am the one that will ask for help in any scenario, where my husband will keep plugging at it until he figures it out for himself.&nbsp; I can't figure out if the basic difference is gender, or if it is 
genetic, or if it is something in how we were raised.&nbsp; 

Many of the men in my current circle of friends also will not ask for directions, preferring to drive around until they stumble upon where they were headed. &nbsp;There are some smart enough to own GPS, of course, but not all. &nbsp;There are also some women I&nbsp;know that refuse to ask for help of any sort, viewing it as a sign of weakness. &nbsp;Regardless of gender, I personally happen to see it as a sign of strength when you can admit that you are lost or have made a mistake, and can freely ask for assistance.
